Test item #19079

- VSCode Version: Code - Insiders 1.9.0-insider (4265f5e35cb3ea8ba7e0cf6b14ec606b6f8647ea, 2017-01-24T10:29:13.076Z)
- OS Version: Darwin x64 15.6.0
- Extensions: None

Steps to Reproduce:

1. Start with:
```
body {
    bgsz
}
```
2. Expand after `z`
3. Type in some size
4. `<enter>`
5. Expected:
```
body {
    -webkit-background-size: 12px;
    background-size: 12px;<caret>
}
```
6. Actual:
```
body {
    -webkit-background-size: 12px<caret>;
    background-size: 12px;
}
```

Same goes for single line expansions, although there it is not as bad because it is just one arrow-left key to correct.
